# Auto parallel work

When the user has **multiple independent requests** or setup can run **parallel to implementation**, launch multiple background subagents **concurrently in ONE message** — don't serialize unnecessarily.

## When to parallelize

- **Independent requests** — e.g. feed fix + nav fix as separate agents if they don't share files or root cause
- **Setup + implementation** — e.g. `git pull` + rule/doc update in parallel when neither needs the other's output
- **Push while user tests** — commit/push can run while the user validates on device; don't block one on the other unless results matter

## When to use ONE agent

Prefer a **single agent** when tasks share context:

- Same files or modules
- Same bug root cause
- Later work needs earlier work's output (types, API shape, investigation findings)

## How to launch

- Send **one message** with multiple `Task` tool calls when subagents are appropriate
- Set `run_in_background: true` when work can proceed without blocking the parent
- **Don't wait** for subagent A to finish before starting B if B doesn't depend on A's output

